records.addlTxt:
Defendant Joshua Davila in court with Attorney John Mathew Krejci.  Erin Michelle Karshen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Matter here for sentencing.  Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  AS TO COUNT #1:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve NINE (9) MONTHS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME.  The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of THREE (3) YEARS.

AS TO COUNT #2:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve SIXTY (60) DAYS in the House of Correction, HUBER FOR WORK, with credit for FOUR (4) DAYS time served FORTHWITH.  

AS TO COUNT #3:  The Court sentenced the defendant to serve NINE (9) MONTHS in the House of Correction, STRAIGHT TIME, CONSECUTIVE.  The Court STAYED this sentence and placed the defendant on probation for a period of THREE (3) YEARS with the following conditions:

1) No contact with the victims, S.D. and E. D.-R.; 
2) Cooperate and participate in SEX OFFENDER EVALUATION and any recommended treatment; 
3) Defendant to advise any and all employers of this case and the specifics of this case;
4) Restitution set at ZERO;
5) Sexual Offender Registry for FIVE (5) years.
6) THREE (3) MONTHS Condition Time--STAYED; 
7) Pay supervision fees;
8) Provide a DNA sample - pay surcharge; 
9) Pay all remaining mandatory costs, fees, surcharges and assessments by the end of probation period or balance to convert to civil judgment;

Court ordered defendant REMANDED into the custody of the Milwaukee County Sheriff's Department.  Matter set for a review hearing on February 16, 2017 at 8:30am in Br. 30, Judge Conen's court.
